'''The Lodge''' is an [[audio mastering]] facility located in Manhattan, New York City. It was founded by [[Emily Lazar]] in 1997.<ref name="bare_url">Boisen, Myles (2003-01-01). "[http://emusician.com/mag/emusic_ears_passion_patience/index.html Ears, Passion, and Patience]" Electronic Musician. Retrieved on 2009-07-17.</ref><ref name="bare_url_a">DiCesare, Ron (2009-03-10). "[http://www.postmagazine.com/Publications/Post-Magazine/2009/March-1-2009/HOW-LOUD-IS-LOUD-.aspx How Loud Is Loud?]" Post Magazine. Retrieved on 2009-07-15.</ref><ref>Walsh, Christopher (2000-09-30)."[http://connection.ebscohost.com/c/articles/3581228/emily-lazars-lodge-stands-out-downtown-n-y Emily Lazar's The Lodge Stands Out In Downtown N.y.]" Billboard. Retrieved on 2009-07-17.</ref><ref>Bender, Brian. [http://www.sonicscoop.com/tag/the-lodge-mastering/#_ "To Mock the Stupendous Mechanism: Designing The Motherbrain’s WSW Console"]. ''SonicScoop'', 13 March 2013.</ref> Over the years The Lodge has mastered recordings for many well known musicians, including [[David Bowie]], [[The Subways]], [[Foo Fighters]],  [[Lou Reed]], [[Paul McCartney]], [[Sinéad O'Connor]], [[Natalie Merchant]],  [[Marianne Faithfull]], and [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]]. The engineers have also mastered sound tracks for movies such as [[American Psycho (film)|American Psycho]] and [[Thievery Corporation]].<ref name="bare_url_a" /><ref>[http://www.sonicscoop.com/tag/the-lodge-mastering/#_ "Session Buzz: Who’s Recording In & Around NYC"]. ''SonicScoop'', 13 March 2013.</ref><ref>(2008-06-09). "[http://www.indymedia.org/pt/2008/06/907796.shtml The Subways bring "All Or Nothing" to The Lodge]" Independent Media Center. Retrieved on 2009-07-17.</ref><ref>Scott, John.[http://www.musicbizacademy.com/articles/gman_mastering.htm "Mastering Your Music".] ''Music Biz Academy'', October 2010.</ref><ref>Schultz, Barbara (2008-02-01). "[http://mixonline.com/recording/mastering/audio_vampires_lodge/ Vampires at the Lodge]" Mix Online. Retrieved on 2009-07-17.</ref><ref>(2001-10-01). "[http://mixonline.com/mag/audio_lodge/ The Lodge]" Mix Online. Retrieved on 2009-07-17.</ref><ref>http://www.allmusic.com/artist/joe-laporta-p619759/credits</ref><ref>http://www.allmusic.com/artist/emily-lazar-p387565/credits</ref>

